---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="About picochem and its author.">
  <main class="about">
    <header class="about-head">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>The project, the author, and how the site is built.</h1>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <h2>The project</h2>
      <p>
        <em>picochem</em> is a personal project: a small encoder-decoder
        transformer for SMILES↔IUPAC translation, built from scratch first in
        pure NumPy and then with hand-written CUDA kernels. The goal was to
        own every line of the stack — tokenizer, ops library, attention,
        backward pass, kernels — so that nothing about a transformer felt
        like a black box.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site collects the write-ups. It is intentionally low on
        ornament: prose, code, a few figures, and citations. If you find
        anything wrong or unclear, I'd like to hear about it.
      </p>

      <h2>About me</h2>
      <p>
        I'm <strong>Arjun Virk</strong>. <em>(Placeholder — replace this
        paragraph with a short bio: where you study or work, what you care
        about, and anything that gives context to the picochem project.)</em>
      </p>

      <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a></li>
        <li><a href="mailto:virkvarjun@gmail.com">Email</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Colophon</h2>
      <p class="text-small text-muted">
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Astro</a>.
        Body text is set in Source Serif 4 at 17px / 1.6; headings and UI in
        Inter; code in JetBrains Mono. The accent is a muted forest green
        (<code>#2d5a3d</code>); the background is a warm off-white
        (<code>#faf8f5</code>). The whole site is static and weighs nearly
        nothing.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    max-width: var(--measure-prose);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem var(--gutter) 1rem;
  }
  .about-head { margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .about-head .eyebrow { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .about-head h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-weight: 600;
    font-size: clamp(1.45rem, 2.5vw, 1.8rem);
    line-height: 1.3;
    letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    color: var(--fg);
    margin: 0;
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
</style>
